# 🚗 Car Price Prediction using Machine Learning

## 📌 Project Overview

This project predicts the selling price of a used car using Machine Learning.

The model analyzes various factors such as car age, fuel type, kilometers driven, transmission type, and ownership history to estimate the selling price.

This project was completed as part of the CodeAlpha Data Science Internship.

---

## 🎯 Objective

To build a Machine Learning regression model that predicts the selling price of used cars based on their features.

---

## 🛠 Technologies Used

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* Scikit-Learn

---

## 📂 Dataset Features

* Car_Name
* Year
* Selling_Price
* Present_Price
* Driven_kms
* Fuel_Type
* Selling_type
* Transmission
* Owner

Target Variable:

* Selling_Price

---

## 📊 Project Workflow

### 1. Data Collection

Loaded the car dataset using Pandas.

### 2. Data Preprocessing

* Checked missing values
* Removed unnecessary columns
* Encoded categorical features

### 3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

* Correlation Heatmap
* Distribution Plots
* Feature Analysis

### 4. Model Training

Used Linear Regression algorithm.

### 5. Model Evaluation

Evaluated using:

* R² Score
* Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
* Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)

---

## 📈 Results

The model successfully predicts used car prices based on vehicle characteristics.

Evaluation Metrics:

* R² Score
* MAE
* RMSE

---

## ▶️ How to Run

```bash
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn scikit-learn
python car_price_prediction.py
```

---

